India-Zimbabwe 4th ODI postponed due to elections

The fourth one-day international of the ongoing series between India and Zimbabwe has been postponed by a day due to general elections in the African country.
The match will now be played at the Queens Sports Club, Bulawayo, on August 1 instead ofthe original date of July 31.
"The fourth ODI of the ongoing series between India and Zimbabwe has been postponed by a day on account of Elections in Zimbabwe," a BCCI release said.
India lead the series 1-0 after defeating the hosts by six wickets in the first one-dayer on Wednesday.

Recruitment of District Legal Aid Officer 

Online Applications are invited at MPOnline Portal from Indian Citizens for posts  in Madhya Pradesh State Legal Service Authority through the Online preliminary exam - on  15/09/2013 and final exam on 27/10/2013  :

How to Apply: Apply Online at MPOnline website up to 12/08/2013 only.
